1
00:01:35,970 --> 00:01:38,310
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,539 --> 00:01:41,310
[Episode 2]

3
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:44,910
Everyone,

4
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:46,310
team up in groups of two.

5
00:01:46,310 --> 00:01:48,000
The winners can skip the 800-meter run.

6
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:48,789
Pick your own partners.

7
00:01:48,789 --> 00:01:49,870
Pick your own partners.

8
00:01:49,870 --> 00:01:50,400
Pick your own partners.

9
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,789
The winners can skip the 800-meter run!

10
00:01:51,789 --> 00:01:53,789
Come on, three groups for the first round.

11
00:01:53,789 --> 00:01:54,789
Let's come up with a chant.

12
00:01:54,789 --> 00:01:57,120
When we move the outside foot,
we shout "one."

13
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,310
When we move the inside foot,
we shout "two."

14
00:01:58,310 --> 00:02:00,230
So it goes: one, two, one, two...

15
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:03,120
Three, two, one.

16
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:03,790
Go!

17
00:02:04,230 --> 00:02:06,150
Come on!

18
00:02:06,150 --> 00:02:07,510
Come on!

19
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:08,400
Tong Xiaole!

20
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:09,400
Come on!

21
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:11,150
Come on!

22
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:12,680
Come on!

23
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:13,960
One, two, one, two.

24
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:14,870
Awesome!

25
00:02:15,590 --> 00:02:17,120
-So amazing!
-Go for it!

26
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,960
Come on, three more groups.

27
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:25,710
Hurry up.

28
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,860
I can get you out of the 800-meter run.

29
00:02:38,630 --> 00:02:39,360
Ready?

30
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,760
Later you follow my call.

31
00:02:45,910 --> 00:02:46,910
For the outside foot, I'll shout "one."

32
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:48,120
For the inside foot, I'll shout "two."

33
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:50,190
Come on. Three, two, one.

34
00:02:50,190 --> 00:02:50,680
Run!

35
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:51,470
Come on!

36
00:02:51,470 --> 00:02:53,030
One, two, one, two.

37
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:54,430
One, two.

38
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,750
One, two.

39
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,960
One, two.

40
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:57,870
One, two.

41
00:03:00,910 --> 00:03:01,800
Sorry.

42
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:04,840
Are you okay?

43
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,240
Yi Lan.

44
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:25,400
You're the best!

45
00:03:25,910 --> 00:03:26,710
Give it to her.

46
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,360
Sorry about what happened just now.

47
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,260
Your stuff's blocking my view of my work.

48
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:49,630
Stand up.

49
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:54,240
Good morning, sir.

50
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:55,240
Luo Ningzi...

51
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,079
You're not going to defend her again,
are you?

52
00:03:57,079 --> 00:03:58,710
Her playing skills are just average.

53
00:03:58,710 --> 00:04:00,110
I'd even say they're bad.

54
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:01,520
Who's bad?

55
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:05,600
Just because I'm bad now
doesn't mean I'll be bad forever.

56
00:04:05,710 --> 00:04:06,710
Luo Ningzi.

57
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,710
How could you say something so harsh?

58
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:09,970
We're all classmates.

59
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:13,000
I'm just telling the truth.

60
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:13,840
Do I

61
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,700
have to make up nice things

62
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:17,190
just to make you happy?

63
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:20,480
Why did you choose

64
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:22,720
the third movement
of Rachmaninoff's Symphony No. 2

65
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:24,270
as your life song?

66
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:27,860
It's in A major.

67
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,830
The melody is beautiful and melancholic.

68
00:04:29,830 --> 00:04:31,360
The harmonies are rich and varied.

69
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,240
And it's one

70
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:35,970
of the most poignant
and aesthetic chapters in music history.

71
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,120
Is that it?

72
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:43,040
Leningrad was being bombed

73
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:45,159
with hundreds of tons
of explosives every day.

74
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:46,510
To pull people through,

75
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,120
musicians performed this symphony

76
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:50,120
for the first time right there in the war.

77
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:52,650
It made everyone believe
that they would win.

78
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,140
That is the power of music.

79
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,120
That's why I tear up whenever I hear it.

80
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,270
It's my life song too.

81
00:05:02,390 --> 00:05:03,950
I thought that having the same life song,

82
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:05,880
we'd feel the same way about music.

83
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:08,390
But that doesn't seem to be the case.

84
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:11,450
Since you don't want to be friends
with me,

85
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:14,370
I don't want to be friends
with you either.

86
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:20,240
Faster.

87
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:28,600
You know what?

88
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:32,680
Joining the school orchestra
requires applying a month in advance.

89
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:34,680
Because you suddenly transferred here,

90
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:36,920
not only did you humiliate Yi Lan
in front of everyone,

91
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:39,510
but you also made her lose her chance
to audition.

92
00:05:39,510 --> 00:05:41,370
Yet she didn't get angry about it.

93
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,680
Instead, she recognized your ability

94
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:44,740
and respected you.

95
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,680
But in my opinion,

96
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,570
your attitude right now

97
00:05:48,830 --> 00:05:50,690
doesn't deserve to be respected.

98
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,920
This... I think

99
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,240
she meant to give it to you.

100
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:11,120
No wonder she doesn't have any friends.

101
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,390
You all look so lifeless.

102
00:06:16,430 --> 00:06:18,430
It's time to switch seats, isn't it?

103
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:22,920
Groups 1 to 4 switch seats
with Groups 5 to 8.

104
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,310
Luo Ningzi,

105
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:25,950
you should be

106
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:26,840
in Group 5.

107
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,600
Five minutes!

108
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,490
Hurry up and switch!

109
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:32,030
Ning, let me help you.

110
00:06:33,630 --> 00:06:34,920
You leg is injured.

111
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:41,480
You're in Group Five,
so you'll be Xiaole's deskmate.

112
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:42,909
Thank you.

113
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,159
Hi, deskmate.

114
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:54,070
Hi, deskmate.

115
00:06:54,070 --> 00:06:54,380
Hi.

116
00:06:54,409 --> 00:06:54,750
Hi.

117
00:06:54,770 --> 00:06:55,120
Hi.

118
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:55,520
Hi.

119
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:56,040
Hi.

120
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,620
Are you free after school?

121
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,450
I want to ask you something.

122
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:08,830
Okay.

123
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:18,600
Traitor.

124
00:07:29,270 --> 00:07:31,270
I'll wait for you at the school gate.

125
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,340
Shall we go?

126
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,580
School's over.

127
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,720
Aren't you going with your new friend?

128
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,520
So... you're not coming with us?

129
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,200
What would I do there while you two chat?

130
00:07:57,270 --> 00:07:57,930
Good point.

131
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:00,160
I'm off then.

132
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:00,920
Go ahead.

133
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,720
You said it.

134
00:08:03,270 --> 00:08:03,750
Yeah.

135
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,240
I'm leaving then.

136
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:08,240
Bye.

137
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:10,950
My new friend!

138
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,160
My new friend!

139
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,360
My new friend!

140
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,560
He's got a new friend now?

141
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,830
Do those two have some kind of secret?

142
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:27,850
Come with me.

143
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:34,080
Later, let's go eat malatang together.

144
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,200
My treat.

145
00:08:42,789 --> 00:08:44,049
Can you slow down a bit?

146
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,600
Is your foot okay?

147
00:08:48,390 --> 00:08:48,990
It's fine.

148
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,480
I can't hear them.

149
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:55,030
When did those two get so close?

150
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:57,200
They're even going home together now.

151
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,330
Why should I believe

152
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,660
what you just said?

153
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:00,960
I mean

154
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,870
why I should believe

155
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,400
that I took Yi Lan's spot.

156
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,280
The school orchestra

157
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:16,600
is basically run by students.

158
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,660
If you don't believe this,

159
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,640
you can go ask anyone.

160
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,000
Why aren't you this impatient

161
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,320
when you talk to them?

162
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,200
The way I talk makes you uncomfortable?

163
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:31,810
That's good.

164
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,150
At least now

165
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:35,120
you know how Yi Lan felt.

166
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:37,960
Childish.

167
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,330
Are you okay?

168
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:54,600
Yi Lan, Mengmeng,

169
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,600
what are you doing here?

170
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,660
You disappeared right after school.

171
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,000
Mengmeng insisted on coming here

172
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,000
to enjoy the view.

173
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,330
What's there to see?

174
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,480
It's really nice.

175
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,440
What were you and Mengmeng

176
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:20,170
furtively looking at just now?

177
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,780
We were enjoying the view.

178
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,080
The view?

179
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:29,810
What's so nice to look at around here?

180
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,200
It's quite nice.

181
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,690
What does it have to do with you?

182
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,320
Are you mad?

183
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,480
Why would I be mad?

184
00:10:40,550 --> 00:10:41,240
I'm not mad.

185
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:45,320
I'm not mad!

186
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:46,630
Fine.

187
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,320
If you're not mad,

188
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,000
get on the bike.

189
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:50,800
Let's go home.

190
00:10:54,630 --> 00:10:55,510
I have legs.

191
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:56,880
I can walk by myself.

192
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,870
You think those two legs of yours

193
00:10:58,870 --> 00:11:00,730
can run faster than my two wheels?

194
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:01,550
Hurry up.

195
00:11:02,630 --> 00:11:03,870
Leave me alone.

196
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:05,490
I can walk by myself.

197
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:07,920
You still say you're not mad?

198
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,200
You're clearly mad.

199
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,200
I said I'm not mad!

200
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,730
Can you stop making conversation
out of nothing?

201
00:11:15,870 --> 00:11:16,600
Fine.

202
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:26,200
When did you

203
00:11:26,510 --> 00:11:27,970
get so close to Luo Ningzi?

204
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:30,200
You know things between her and me
are awkward.

205
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,200
You're betraying me, you know that?

206
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,520
Do you still want to play cello with her?

207
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,440
What does it have to do with you?

208
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:48,390
Yeah.

209
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,930
It indeed has nothing to do with me.

210
00:11:51,670 --> 00:11:53,200
Walk home by yourself then.

211
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:57,900
You're actually leaving?

212
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:10,280
Do you still want to play cello with her?

213
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,870
It's lunch break, right?

214
00:12:21,870 --> 00:12:23,670
Alright, arrange your own time.

215
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,510
Don't erase the blackboard.

216
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:26,640
We'll continue this afternoon, okay?

217
00:12:27,030 --> 00:12:28,120
Don't run around!

218
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,320
Class dismissed.

219
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:32,850
Come with me.

220
00:12:33,030 --> 00:12:34,160
I need to talk to you.

221
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:40,950
Go eat by yourself first.

222
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:43,700
Qiao Mengmeng.

223
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:00,360
You lost.

224
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,000
That doesn't count.

225
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,000
Let's do it again.

226
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:11,100
Zhao Zhenghao, let me ask you something.

227
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:12,960
Are there auditions
for the school orchestra?

228
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,000
Why did you cancel Yi Lan's audition?

229
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:15,860
What audition?

230
00:13:21,630 --> 00:13:22,120
Don't tell me

231
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:24,240
you're actually sympathizing with her.

232
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:25,300
It's not sympathy.

233
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,880
I want to compete fairly,

234
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,410
even if she still loses.

235
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:35,870
There's no such thing as fair competition.

236
00:13:35,870 --> 00:13:37,960
I decide who it is!

237
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:41,060
Since you're the captain,

238
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:43,610
you should consider
your members' opinions.

239
00:13:43,870 --> 00:13:44,600
Besides,

240
00:13:44,870 --> 00:13:46,470
I was just nervous last time.

241
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,200
If you've got the guts,

242
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,440
let me play again.

243
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:51,770
Otherwise, I'll leave too.

244
00:13:54,550 --> 00:13:56,200
Then let's just set another time.

245
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:56,720
Right?

246
00:13:58,870 --> 00:13:59,440
Fine.

247
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,720
Since you want to prove yourself so badly,

248
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,380
I'll give you another chance.

249
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:06,300
Next Monday,
see you in the music room after school.

250
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,200
Thanks.

251
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:21,440
After school.

252
00:14:21,630 --> 00:14:23,030
See you in the music room.

253
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:24,480
See you in the music room.

254
00:14:33,870 --> 00:14:35,600
Why are you smiling so happily?

255
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,290
I'm happy whenever you're around.

256
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:43,930
The basketball!

257
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:58,600
Xiaole!

258
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,080
So you're at home.

259
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,440
Why didn't you answer the phone?

260
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,900
I called you so many times.

261
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,250
I didn't hear it.

262
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,060
Move over a bit.

263
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,750
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

264
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:18,360
No.

265
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:23,360
I'll cook for you in a bit.

266
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,880
I need to rest for a while.

267
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:51,440
Mom, I'm going out.

268
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:55,290
Why are you so inconsiderate?

269
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:57,600
It's already this late,
and you're still going out?

270
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,660
Your mom just said she'd cook for you!

271
00:16:01,550 --> 00:16:02,440
Are you mute?

272
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:03,860
Say something!

273
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:06,790
Oh.

274
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:09,080
What kind of attitude is that?

275
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:10,870
You never answer your mom's calls!

276
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:13,070
Do you know how worried she was just now?

277
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:13,750
Alright, alright.

278
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:15,680
You always make such a mess at home.

279
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:18,000
Every time your mom has to clean it up
after she gets home!

280
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,000
It's fine, really.

281
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,060
Alright, alright.

282
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:21,550
Give it a rest.

283
00:16:21,630 --> 00:16:22,440
Give it a rest?

284
00:16:22,550 --> 00:16:24,200
Today, I'm going to let him know

285
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,080
that I am his father!

286
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,240
He can't just do whatever he wants

287
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,200
in this family!

288
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,000
So you do remember you're my father!

289
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,200
All you care about is your lousy money!

290
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,550
Have you ever cared about me?

291
00:16:31,550 --> 00:16:33,320
Have you ever been
to my parent-teacher conferences?

292
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,720
Have you ever cared
about what I do

293
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:35,980
or what I eat at school?

294
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:36,720
Look at yourself!

295
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:37,870
What right do you have to lecture me?

296
00:16:37,870 --> 00:16:39,270
Because I'm your father!

297
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:41,320
I work my ass off to support this family!

298
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,650
This is how you repay me?

299
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:44,360
Stop it.

300
00:16:44,870 --> 00:16:45,480
Stop it.

301
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:46,240
Just get out.

302
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:46,700
Get out.

303
00:16:47,630 --> 00:16:48,890
Who are you glaring at?

304
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:50,160
You ungrateful brat!

305
00:17:56,840 --> 00:18:04,860
[Come get some fried chicken, same place]
[Come quickly!]

306
00:18:04,890 --> 00:18:08,470
[Okay]

307
00:18:39,070 --> 00:18:40,600
It's really boring, Yi Lan.

308
00:18:41,790 --> 00:18:43,270
You're so boring.

309
00:18:45,550 --> 00:18:47,110
How come you started eating without me?

310
00:18:47,110 --> 00:18:48,110
It smells so good.

311
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:49,030
Try one.

312
00:18:49,350 --> 00:18:50,310
Have a bite!

313
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:56,920
Are you okay?

314
00:18:58,270 --> 00:18:58,830
I'm good.

315
00:18:59,030 --> 00:18:59,750
I'm great.

316
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,590
He picks on me
every time he comes home anyway.

317
00:19:01,590 --> 00:19:02,400
I'm used to it.

318
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:06,830
It's okay.

319
00:19:06,830 --> 00:19:07,920
Don't be upset.

320
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:10,550
Your hands are all greasy.

321
00:19:10,550 --> 00:19:11,550
So what?

322
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,070
Just come to me whenever you're unhappy.

323
00:19:16,070 --> 00:19:16,830
Don't keep it to yourself.

324
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:17,890
I'll stay with you.

325
00:19:19,030 --> 00:19:19,490
Really?

326
00:19:19,510 --> 00:19:20,030
Yeah.

327
00:19:23,110 --> 00:19:24,270
What are you doing?

328
00:19:24,510 --> 00:19:25,570
You're in trouble!

329
00:20:10,110 --> 00:20:11,310
Xiaole, you're back.

330
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:12,970
Yeah, I'm back.

331
00:20:13,310 --> 00:20:14,110
Mom, I'm going to sleep.

332
00:20:14,110 --> 00:20:15,160
You should rest early too.

333
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:15,830
Okay.

334
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:44,550
I'm here!

335
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:46,030
Didn't you say you were going
to do homework?

336
00:20:46,030 --> 00:20:48,090
Why are you carrying your cello case?

337
00:20:48,350 --> 00:20:50,310
I obviously need to practice hard.

338
00:20:50,310 --> 00:20:52,550
I have to do well
at the school orchestra audition.

339
00:20:52,550 --> 00:20:53,400
Fine.

340
00:20:54,030 --> 00:20:55,000
Aren't you gonna help me carry it?

341
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,460
Just toss it in the basket.

342
00:21:11,350 --> 00:21:12,810
There's some weird noise.

343
00:21:15,790 --> 00:21:17,050
Let me check it for you.

344
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:18,930
Give it to me.

345
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:20,750
Make yourself comfortable.

346
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:22,550
Someone's practicing in there.

347
00:21:43,790 --> 00:21:45,440
She doesn't even need the sheet music.

348
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:46,700
Pretty talented, huh?

349
00:21:49,830 --> 00:21:50,920
Leave your cello here.

350
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:52,780
I'll let you know when it's fixed.

351
00:21:53,070 --> 00:21:53,680
Thanks.

352
00:21:53,790 --> 00:21:54,450
No problem.

353
00:21:54,590 --> 00:21:55,350
Take care.

354
00:21:56,190 --> 00:21:59,000
♪ Looking forward
to the next beautiful dream ♪

355
00:21:59,050 --> 00:22:00,490
♪ I just want to be with you ♪

356
00:21:59,200 --> 00:21:59,790
This girl

357
00:22:00,730 --> 00:22:03,530
♪ To see the most romantic starry sky
together ♪

358
00:22:00,790 --> 00:22:02,320
doesn't even like to smile.

359
00:22:03,970 --> 00:22:07,920
♪ The evening breeze tells
heartfelt emotions ♪

360
00:22:08,870 --> 00:22:10,520
♪ All the stars surround you ♪

361
00:22:10,540 --> 00:22:12,190
♪ The moon smiles at you ♪

362
00:22:12,220 --> 00:22:15,440
♪ I give you all the good things
in the world ♪

363
00:22:15,910 --> 00:22:17,400
♪ And the light in your eyes ♪

364
00:22:17,420 --> 00:22:19,500
♪ Shines like diamonds ♪

365
00:22:19,930 --> 00:22:22,650
♪ Drawing an exclamation mark
in my world ♪

366
00:22:22,790 --> 00:22:24,170
♪ The evening breeze embraces you ♪

367
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:25,990
♪ And I run towards you ♪

368
00:22:26,130 --> 00:22:29,480
♪ I hear our passionate heartbeats ♪

369
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:31,070
♪ We borrow a dream ♪

370
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:33,370
♪ To build a castle ♪

371
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:36,010
♪ Every star is a romantic symbol ♪

372
00:22:36,070 --> 00:22:37,830
Lan, that was beautiful!

373
00:22:36,130 --> 00:22:38,600
♪ Let me find you ♪

374
00:22:41,070 --> 00:22:42,070
Thanks.

375
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:45,070
Why work so hard?

376
00:22:45,070 --> 00:22:46,590
You'll lose to Luo Ningzi anyway.

377
00:22:46,590 --> 00:22:47,720
Shut your trap.

378
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:49,350
I was just joking.

379
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,070
Anyway, I just need to show

380
00:22:52,070 --> 00:22:53,830
my true ability.

381
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:55,490
I don't care about the rest.

382
00:25:14,590 --> 00:25:16,190
That's just beginner level.

383
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:18,200
With this,

384
00:25:18,750 --> 00:25:20,880
she can get into our school orchestra?

385
00:25:21,070 --> 00:25:21,920
Indeed.

386
00:25:22,110 --> 00:25:24,110
Yi Lan, your level...

387
00:25:26,830 --> 00:25:28,360
What do you say, Luo Ningzi?

388
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:36,450
Her understanding of music

389
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,200
is more than qualified

390
00:25:39,110 --> 00:25:40,640
for your school orchestra.

391
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:42,590
What do you mean,

392
00:25:42,590 --> 00:25:43,250
Luo Ningzi?

393
00:25:44,350 --> 00:25:45,270
It's okay.

394
00:25:45,830 --> 00:25:48,110
I know everyone's really good.

395
00:25:48,550 --> 00:25:49,680
I don't care

396
00:25:50,310 --> 00:25:53,110
if I can make it
into the school orchestra anymore.

397
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:01,610
Zhao Zhenghao, you're such a jerk!

398
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:05,110
Let's go.

399
00:26:05,110 --> 00:26:05,970
Zhao Zhenghao.

400
00:26:06,350 --> 00:26:08,510
The school orchestra
doesn't belong to you alone.

401
00:26:08,510 --> 00:26:09,350
If the school orchestra

402
00:26:09,350 --> 00:26:11,200
is full of people like you
who don't respect music

403
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,200
and are arrogant,

404
00:26:12,830 --> 00:26:13,590
then I don't see

405
00:26:13,590 --> 00:26:15,720
any point in this orchestra existing.

406
00:26:22,750 --> 00:26:24,070
I... I didn't mean it.

407
00:26:31,110 --> 00:26:32,970
Everyone, just keep practicing.

408
00:26:45,790 --> 00:26:46,510
Sorry.

409
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:55,550
Mengmeng,

410
00:26:55,550 --> 00:26:57,310
isn't this a bit too much?

411
00:26:57,590 --> 00:26:59,030
You even got me a wheelchair.

412
00:26:59,030 --> 00:26:59,790
Absolutely.

413
00:26:59,790 --> 00:27:01,850
I'm terrified you'll get hurt again.

414
00:27:02,030 --> 00:27:02,830
But Lan,

415
00:27:02,830 --> 00:27:05,690
why didn't you join the school orchestra
in the end?

416
00:27:06,110 --> 00:27:07,910
Luo Ningzi is indeed excellent.

417
00:27:08,110 --> 00:27:09,750
But at least I've proved to her

418
00:27:09,750 --> 00:27:11,830
that I'm not that bad. And that's enough.

419
00:27:11,830 --> 00:27:12,510
Fine.

420
00:27:12,550 --> 00:27:14,550
Anyway, you're the best in my heart.

421
00:27:14,590 --> 00:27:16,350
You are so sweet, Mengmeng.

422
00:27:16,350 --> 00:27:17,790
Of course, Lan.

423
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:19,790
Why does it take so long

424
00:27:19,790 --> 00:27:21,920
for Chen Fan and Xiaole to buy skewers?

425
00:27:34,550 --> 00:27:35,920
What exactly do you want?

426
00:27:35,920 --> 00:27:37,580
Why are you always against me?

427
00:27:38,590 --> 00:27:39,270
Don't tell me you want

428
00:27:39,270 --> 00:27:41,600
to be the captain of the school orchestra.

429
00:27:45,350 --> 00:27:47,110
I knew that was your plan.

430
00:27:47,590 --> 00:27:50,250
You wanted to humiliate me
in front of everyone.

431
00:27:54,070 --> 00:27:55,550
Are you questioning me?

432
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:57,050
Let me tell you this.

433
00:27:57,110 --> 00:28:00,310
Without me, the school orchestra
wouldn't be what it is today.

434
00:28:00,310 --> 00:28:01,830
I worked my ass off

435
00:28:02,030 --> 00:28:04,830
to get every single instrument
in this orchestra.

436
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:06,790
To me, the orchestra

437
00:28:07,110 --> 00:28:08,550
is my territory

438
00:28:09,110 --> 00:28:10,160
and my king!

439
00:28:14,510 --> 00:28:15,350
My kingdom!

440
00:28:23,510 --> 00:28:25,310
How can you be so disrespectful?

441
00:28:30,110 --> 00:28:31,070
Luo Ningzi?

442
00:28:31,680 --> 00:28:32,310
Let's go.

443
00:28:32,590 --> 00:28:33,720
Let's go have a look.

444
00:28:34,350 --> 00:28:35,590
I am talking to you!

445
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:42,250
Stop it, Zhao Zhenghao!

446
00:28:42,830 --> 00:28:43,510
Mengmeng.

447
00:28:46,790 --> 00:28:48,050
You called for backup?

448
00:28:48,110 --> 00:28:50,030
Zhao Zhenghao, I'm warning you.

449
00:28:50,110 --> 00:28:51,110
Don't think just because we're off campus,

450
00:28:51,110 --> 00:28:52,110
you can do whatever you want.

451
00:28:52,110 --> 00:28:52,750
Exactly!

452
00:28:53,110 --> 00:28:54,830
I never laid my hands on girls.

453
00:28:55,550 --> 00:28:57,160
But you've gone too far.

454
00:28:57,920 --> 00:28:59,980
You're practically forcing my hand.

455
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:03,500
What are you doing?

456
00:29:04,350 --> 00:29:04,810
This...

457
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:05,930
Is anyone there?

458
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:06,920
Help!

459
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:09,200
-Help!
-Let go of her!

460
00:29:22,110 --> 00:29:22,680
What kind of man

461
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:24,200
picks on three girls?

462
00:29:24,750 --> 00:29:26,610
What does this have to do with you?

463
00:29:26,830 --> 00:29:28,110
Mind your own business.

464
00:29:28,110 --> 00:29:29,710
Of course it has to do with me.

465
00:29:29,830 --> 00:29:32,070
They're all under my protection.

466
00:29:32,510 --> 00:29:34,770
When you mess with them, you mess with me.

467
00:29:36,790 --> 00:29:37,350
Fine.

468
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:40,350
Then let's fight like real men.

469
00:29:45,680 --> 00:29:46,440
For real?

470
00:29:50,790 --> 00:29:51,250
Come on.

471
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:52,310
Come on.

472
00:30:00,310 --> 00:30:00,770
Come on.

473
00:30:00,830 --> 00:30:01,290
Come on.

474
00:30:04,830 --> 00:30:05,560
He's so weak.

475
00:30:07,110 --> 00:30:07,680
Captain Zhao!

476
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:08,680
Zhenghao!

477
00:30:09,270 --> 00:30:09,830
Zhenghao!

478
00:30:09,830 --> 00:30:10,430
Zhenghao!

479
00:30:11,350 --> 00:30:12,240
Help me up.

480
00:30:14,030 --> 00:30:14,680
Run!

481
00:30:16,070 --> 00:30:16,750
Hurry!

482
00:30:16,830 --> 00:30:18,510
Guys, what took you so long?

483
00:30:19,200 --> 00:30:20,060
Where are they?

484
00:30:20,200 --> 00:30:21,060
Where are they?

485
00:30:21,830 --> 00:30:23,360
They called for backup too?

486
00:30:26,550 --> 00:30:27,950
Zhenghao, they ran away.

487
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:29,400
Should we chase them?

488
00:30:29,830 --> 00:30:30,510
Of course!

489
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:31,580
After them!

490
00:30:31,590 --> 00:30:31,990
Quick!

491
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:33,830
Director Hu,

492
00:30:33,830 --> 00:30:34,750
it's them!

493
00:30:34,790 --> 00:30:35,520
Director Hu,

494
00:30:36,510 --> 00:30:37,510
they're bullying us.

495
00:30:37,510 --> 00:30:38,070
Are you okay?

496
00:30:38,070 --> 00:30:38,600
It's him!

497
00:30:39,510 --> 00:30:40,830
You little brats,

498
00:30:41,350 --> 00:30:42,110
stop right there!

499
00:30:42,110 --> 00:30:43,350
You punks!

500
00:30:44,310 --> 00:30:44,920
Which class are you from?

501
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:46,200
Don't let me catch you!

502
00:30:46,350 --> 00:30:47,350
Stop right there!

503
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:53,060
Zhao Zhenghao!

504
00:30:55,310 --> 00:30:56,310
Stop right there!

505
00:31:08,110 --> 00:31:09,370
Tong Xiaole, Chen Fan!

506
00:31:10,750 --> 00:31:11,610
Come over here.

507
00:31:13,590 --> 00:31:14,520
And you guys too?

508
00:31:18,310 --> 00:31:18,910
Mengmeng,

509
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:20,200
you're such a traitor.

510
00:31:20,200 --> 00:31:21,680
You ran off by yourself.

511
00:31:21,830 --> 00:31:23,830
I just went to get help.

512
00:31:28,110 --> 00:31:29,400
Look at you two.

513
00:31:29,550 --> 00:31:31,280
Did you really become besties?

514
00:31:32,310 --> 00:31:33,070
Luo Ningzi.

515
00:31:33,350 --> 00:31:35,350
Although you don't like making friends,

516
00:31:35,350 --> 00:31:37,200
you're still a good friend.

517
00:31:42,200 --> 00:31:44,000
Can I invite you

518
00:31:44,070 --> 00:31:46,590
to practice cello with me after school?

519
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,790
After school, I usually

520
00:31:51,790 --> 00:31:54,450
practice in the school music room
for two hours.

521
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:56,030
Oh.

522
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:00,110
But the school doesn't say

523
00:32:00,110 --> 00:32:02,040
only orchestra members can use it.

524
00:32:04,550 --> 00:32:06,880
Then let's practice together from now on.

525
00:32:11,270 --> 00:32:11,870
Together!

526
00:32:15,590 --> 00:32:16,120
Let's go.

527
00:32:21,310 --> 00:32:21,920
Director,

528
00:32:22,310 --> 00:32:23,310
it was him.

529
00:32:23,350 --> 00:32:24,270
He led

530
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:24,960
them...

531
00:32:25,310 --> 00:32:26,070
these guys...

532
00:32:26,070 --> 00:32:27,800
They cornered us after school.

533
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:29,000
And my leg

534
00:32:29,070 --> 00:32:29,730
got injured

535
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,020
because of him.

536
00:32:32,270 --> 00:32:33,350
It had nothing to do with those two?

537
00:32:33,350 --> 00:32:33,790
Nothing!

538
00:32:33,790 --> 00:32:34,650
Nothing at all.

539
00:32:35,830 --> 00:32:36,360
Alright.

540
00:32:37,070 --> 00:32:38,600
I've got the whole picture.

541
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:40,260
Tong Xiaole, Chen Fan,

542
00:32:40,310 --> 00:32:41,510
you two are innocent.

543
00:32:41,790 --> 00:32:42,390
You can go.

544
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:43,590
Thank you, Director.

545
00:32:43,590 --> 00:32:44,790
Thank you, Director.

546
00:32:44,830 --> 00:32:46,030
Director, then we...

547
00:32:46,110 --> 00:32:46,710
You can go.

548
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:53,610
Stand still!

549
00:32:55,830 --> 00:32:57,830
You guys like causing trouble, huh?

550
00:32:58,110 --> 00:32:58,590
Fine.

551
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:01,000
As your punishment,
you'll clean the toilets

552
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:01,790
for a week!

553
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:04,640
Try playing it first.

554
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,810
Let me take a listen.

555
00:33:16,750 --> 00:33:17,270
Stop.

556
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:22,170
Count the beat in your head.

557
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,260
You have to keep up.

558
00:33:24,270 --> 00:33:24,950
Da, da, da, da.

559
00:33:24,950 --> 00:33:25,540
Da, da, da, da.

560
00:33:25,540 --> 00:33:26,150
Da, da, da, da.

561
00:33:26,150 --> 00:33:26,950
Da, da, da, da.

562
00:33:27,270 --> 00:33:28,530
Keep the tempo steady.

563
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:30,270
Five, six, seven, go!

564
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:31,400
Da, da, da, da.

565
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:32,000
Da, da, da, da.

566
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:32,690
Da, da, da, da.

567
00:33:32,690 --> 00:33:33,440
Da, da, da, da.

568
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:33,830
Stop.

569
00:33:36,070 --> 00:33:37,550
You're falling behind the tempo a bit.

570
00:33:37,550 --> 00:33:39,750
You might need to practice more at home.

571
00:33:41,440 --> 00:33:43,200
Separate your second and third fingers
a bit more.

572
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:44,330
Curve your fingers.

573
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:47,680
Stop.

574
00:33:49,070 --> 00:33:51,350
You still need more practice at home.

575
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:23,440
What?

576
00:34:24,070 --> 00:34:24,760
Give me one.

577
00:34:25,070 --> 00:34:26,130
This is not for you.

578
00:34:26,190 --> 00:34:27,670
You have so many,
but I can't even have one?

579
00:34:27,670 --> 00:34:28,760
Haven't you eaten enough?

580
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:29,290
Get lost.

581
00:34:34,150 --> 00:34:35,800
Then it must be for me.

582
00:34:38,590 --> 00:34:39,920
It's not for you either.

583
00:34:41,550 --> 00:34:42,550
Then who is it for?

584
00:34:42,710 --> 00:34:44,190
It's for Ning.

585
00:34:44,510 --> 00:34:45,670
Ning?

586
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:47,760
You call her Ning?

587
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:51,250
This morning you called me Qiao Mengmeng!

588
00:34:51,670 --> 00:34:52,400
Mengmeng.

589
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:53,080
Mengmeng.

590
00:34:55,320 --> 00:34:56,580
She's your new friend?

591
00:34:57,630 --> 00:34:59,190
She is my new friend,

592
00:34:59,550 --> 00:35:01,150
but you are my best friend.

593
00:35:01,150 --> 00:35:02,000
It's different.

594
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,600
Then where does a best friend

595
00:35:04,510 --> 00:35:05,550
rank?

596
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,670
Ranked first.

597
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:08,480
First.

598
00:35:11,550 --> 00:35:12,400
Only one.

599
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:17,760
Ning.

600
00:35:19,510 --> 00:35:21,150
This nougat is really good.

601
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,130
It's for you.

602
00:35:24,630 --> 00:35:25,360
Thanks.

603
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:28,920
This is

604
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:30,170
for you.

605
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:32,780
It's also a collector's edition.

606
00:35:36,490 --> 00:35:38,910
[Rachmaninoff's Symphony No. 2]
